      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LAMBRO MACH (5) appreciated the inside barrier when he scored last time out by 7.7 metres in a nice return to form at this circuit and distance. Draws wider but finds another suitable assignment so could go on with it. ISOLATION (7) is in fine form, winning his past two outings here. Settled close to the pace and finished too well to score by more than 5 metres last week. Draws wider but with even luck he could land the hat trick. KIA ORA BEAUTY (9) could be close to a win after placing in two of her last three starts, coming from this barrier for third last time out at Bendigo. JACCKA CONNOR NZ (1) has been thereabouts from wide or second line draws so is worth some thought from the inside barrier.",
